source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000010_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>The people of this city have spirit, I'll give them that. They've not lost the will to fight.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000010_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Les habitants d'ici sont bien résilients. Malgré tout ce qui s'est passé, leur volonté de se battre est restée intacte.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000020_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I can imagine how torn you must feel, looking at that sky. Knowing what it means to everyone...and that you're responsible.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000020_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Ça ne doit pas être facile pour toi... d'être à l'origine de tout cela...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q1_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q1_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que répondez-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A1_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>The secrecy is worse. I'd rather people knew.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A1_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Mieux vaut que la population n'en sache rien.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A1_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>I still can't believe it's coming from me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A1_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>J'ai du mal à croire que ça vienne de moi.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A1_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>It's all such a mess.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A1_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>Je n'ai pas envie d'en parler.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000030_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>If you're thinking of coming clean, don't. It might make <var 1A 02 /var>you<var 1A 01 /var> feel better, but it would make things a hundred times worse for them. They're better off not knowing.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000030_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Tu as sans doute raison. Lui dire la vérité ne ferait qu'accroître son désarroi. Elle mérite mieux que ça.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000040_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab><sigh> Neither can I, to be honest.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000040_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je m'en doute... À vrai dire, j'ai moi-même l'impression que tu n'y es pour rien.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000050_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>But you heard what the Ascian said: the Light you shine will warp the world around you whether you like it or not. Even Y'shtola and Ryne had to concede that point.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000050_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Mais Emet-Selch a bien précisé que ta seule présence suffirait à inonder ce monde de Lumière. D'ailleurs, Y'shtola et Ryne se sont penchées sur ton cas, mais aucune n'est parvenue à stopper le phénomène.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000060_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Aye. An all too familiar one. Here you stand alone, expecting no one else to bear the burden for you.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000060_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je sais ce que tu ressens. Et j'admire le fait que tu tiennes bon, même seul<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> face à l'adversité.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000070_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>You're in a corner, and there doesn't seem to be any obvious way out.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000070_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je ne te cacherai pas que la situation est critique. Je ne vois aucune échappatoire à ce pétrin.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000080_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>...But that doesn't mean it's over. However hopeless it seems, you haven't lost yet.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000080_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Mais même au fond du gouffre, il reste toujours de l'espoir. Il est encore trop tôt pour baisser les bras, tu ne crois pas<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000090_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I remember looking up at the sky like this before─being caught up in a strange kind of calm.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000090_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je me souviens... la dernière fois que j'ai contemplé le ciel avec cet étrange sentiment de quiétude dans mon cœur...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000100_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>It was after we realized we were responsible for the Flood. When we resolved to journey to the Source by taking our own lives.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000100_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>C'était en apprenant que mes camarades et moi étions res<var 16 /var>pon<var 16 /var>sa<var 16 /var>bles du déluge de Lumière... Juste avant que nous ne mettions fin à nos jours dans le but d'atteindre le monde primitif.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000110_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>One last sacrifice, one last fight...one last failure. And then the Oracle appeared and...well. You know the rest.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000110_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Là-bas, vous nous avez affrontés et vaincus, tes camarades et toi... Par chance, la prêtresse de la Lumière a sauvé nos âmes juste avant qu'elles ne s'éteignent, empêchant ainsi la destruction totale de notre monde.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000120_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>There were times in the years and decades that followed when I wondered if we might not've been better off just letting the Rejoining happen.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000120_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>J'ignorais si ce qu'il m'était arrivé était une chance ou une malédiction. Plutôt que de survivre sous cette forme bâtarde, j'aurais peut-être préféré ne faire plus qu'un avec Hydaelyn...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000130_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>That we'd made one last mistake...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000130_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Et pourtant...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000140_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>But seeing that giant Talos stir to life cured me of any doubts I still had.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000140_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Sur Kholusia, lorsque vous avez mis en marche ce talos géant, j'ai ressenti une vive émotion. C'était... de la joie.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000150_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Always. Always we took the burden of fighting upon ourselves. That's what heroes do, isn't it?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000150_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Mes amis et moi, on a toujours refusé de compter sur les autres. On avait la conviction que c'était à nous de lutter pour le peuple, et pas le contraire.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000160_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>So we never had the chance to see anything like that─our people, coming together as one.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000160_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je ne m'attendais pas à voir autant de monde travailler de concert. Pour moi, c'était une première.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000170_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>To think that their hope still burned so bright...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000170_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>C'était tellement beau à voir... L'émotion m'étreignait si fort que je ne pouvais plus dire un mot.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000180_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>...That they were still so eager to live, they would lift up their fellows, one on top of the other, till they reached the sky.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000180_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>J'ai réalisé que des milliers de gens n'avaient qu'un désir, celui de vivre dans ce monde. Que tous ensemble, ils pouvaient réaliser l'impossible.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000190_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>No, we made the right decision. And I can finally feel proud of the part we played in helping this world survive.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000190_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>J'avais eu raison de me battre pour que ce futur arrive. Pour la première fois, j'étais fier de ce que j'avais accompli.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000200_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Well? Come on, then!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000200_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Dans ces moments-là, il faut se cogner les poings<var 1D /var>! Allez<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000210_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>As I thought. What happened between us was no coincidence.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000210_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>C'est bien ce que je pensais. Ce qui s'est passé l'autre fois n'était pas un hasard.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000220_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>My story may be finished, but the fates have gifted me a minor role in yours.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000220_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je ne suis plus en mesure de sauver le monde, c'est certain. Mais va savoir pourquoi, je suis capable d'interagir avec toi. Le destin, peut-être...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000230_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I suspected as much the moment I realized you could hear me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000230_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je m'en doutais un peu, étant donné qu'on peut se voir et se parler.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000240_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>But it's hard not to doubt yourself when you're the man who caused the Flood...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000240_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Dans tous les cas, je reste le principal responsable du déluge de Lumière, et toutes les excuses du monde n'y changeront rien.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000250_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I was afraid to do anything more than watch for fear of making things even worse...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000250_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>À cause de ça, j'ai constamment peur de regretter mes actes... Je suis incapable de me fier à mon propre jugement, et ça m'empêche d'aller de l'avant.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000260_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>...But no longer. After all, the path I once walked is now yours to finish.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000260_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Heu<var 16 /var>reu<var 16 /var>se<var 16 /var>ment que vous m'avez prouvé que mes choix n'étaient pas tous mauvais. Grâce à vous, je me sens assez fort pour prêter un nouveau serment.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000270_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>For what it's worth, I cast my lot with yours.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000270_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je choisis de croire en toi, en mon âme et conscience. Même si je ne suis plus que l'ombre de moi-même, je t'aiderai du mieux que je le peux.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000280_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>If you need a push, I'll be right there behind you; if you lose control, I'll do my best to stop you.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000280_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Si tu deviens l'ennemi<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> de ce monde, je tâcherai de te ramener à la raison. Si tu te bats pour lui, je t'encouragerai.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000290_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>So─let us be about it, <var 1A 02 /var>hero<var 1A 01 /var>.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000290_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>La balle est dans ton camp, alors va, brave <var 08 E905 ((héroïne)) ((héros)) /var>.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000300_FEOUL<tab>I was worried you were up here all alone, brooding and fretting and wallowing in your woes. But look at you─grinning at nothing like a pollen-drunk pixie!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000300_FEOUL<tab>(-Voix familière-)Tiens tiens... Je viens voir si mon arbrisseau va bien, et je le retrouve tout sourire, les yeux dans le vague... Aurait-il perdu la tête<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000310_FEOUL<tab>Hmph! Look at what you've done to your aether! It's a mess! And you have cracks running all through that pretty soul of yours!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000310_FEOUL<tab>Beurk... Ton éther est com<var 16 /var>plè<var 16 /var>te<var 16 /var>ment chamboulé... Et ton âme, on dirait qu'on vient de la rapiécer<var 1D /var>! Ça ne va pas du tout<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000320_FEOUL<tab>My poor little sapling. Whatever am I to do with you?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000320_FEOUL<tab>Mon pauvre... Que comptes-tu faire maintenant<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000330_FEOUL<tab>Shall I yield up my throne? You could claim it─cut ties with the mortal world, hide away in the castle...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000330_FEOUL<tab>Et si tu devenais notre nouveau monarque<var 1D /var>? Tu couperais les ponts avec les humains et tu vivrais bien à l'abri dans ton château.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000340_FEOUL<tab>It won't fix the problem...but would it really matter? If any pesky heroes come calling with steel and magic, all of Il Mheg will rise up in your defense.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000340_FEOUL<tab>Ça ne résoudrait rien, mais au moins ce serait confortable. Et puis le peuple féérique pourra te protéger si quelqu'un réclame ta tête.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000350_FEOUL<tab>My crown and scepter are yours...if you want them.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000350_FEOUL<tab>Je te donne ma couronne et mon sceptre si tu veux<var 1D /var>! Qu'est-ce que t'en dis<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000360_FEOUL<tab>What? Don't give me that look! Of course I knew before I asked that you'd never ever heed such a <var 1A 02 /var>wicked<var 1A 01 /var> suggestion!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000360_FEOUL<tab>C'est bon, j'ai compris<var 1D /var>! Pff, je me creuse la tête pour trouver des solutions, et mon arbrisseau ne veut même pas en entendre parler. Sans-cœur un jour, sans-cœur toujours<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000370_FEOUL<tab>And besides, what would become of my precious and ephemeral flower?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000370_FEOUL<tab>Enfin, ce n'est pas plus mal que tu aies refusé. Tu aurais perdu un peu de ton charme en devenant notre souverain<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var>, héhé.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000380_FEOUL<tab>My dear, beloved sapling. You are lost─confused─and have precious little time to gather your wits.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000380_FEOUL<tab>Dis, dis, mon mignon petit arbrisseau... On dirait que tu t'es perdu en cours de route. Tu vas devoir retrouver ton chemin rapidement.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000390_FEOUL<tab>Your kind is always so preoccupied with what lies ahead, and so we muddle your vision with fog and glamour. But such trickery is easy to see through.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000390_FEOUL<tab>Quand les humains sont égarés, ils essaient en général d'aller droit devant eux. Et nous, on fait apparaître du brouillard ou des illusions pour les faire tourner en bourrique.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000400_FEOUL<tab>Stand very, very still. Think not of where you need to go, but where you are right now at this moment. At this time, in this place...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000400_FEOUL<tab>Le secret pour s'en sortir, ce n'est pas d'avancer au hasard... mais de s'arrêter et de regarder autour de soi. Pour savoir où on va, il faut d'abord savoir d'où on vient.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000410_FEOUL<tab>Our [friend] of crystal. From shadowed hood he watched you go, his ruby eyes with warmth aglow.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000410_FEOUL<tab>Notre <var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>ami<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var> de cristal... Son œil vermeil a suivi tout ton parcours. À aucun moment, il n'a cessé de veiller sur toi.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000420_FEOUL<tab>See yourself as he saw you, and that shall be the clearest clue.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000420_FEOUL<tab>Essaie de cerner ses intentions, c'est ta meilleure chance d'en apprendre plus sur toi-même. Ainsi, tu sauras exactement où tu te trouves en ce moment précis.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000430_FEOUL<tab>You stand in his garden, dear sapling. Ask his flowers what they know, and you will surely find an answer.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000430_FEOUL<tab>Ça tombe bien, c'est son sanctuaire, ici. Ses habitants devraient pouvoir te renseigner.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000440_FEOUL<tab>But what will you do with it, I wonder...? I'll be watching and waiting, waiting and watching!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000440_FEOUL<tab>Quant à moi, je continuerai à te suivre, peu importe tes choix... Sur ce, je te dis à la prochaine.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000450_LYNA<tab>I have unlocked the door to the Umbilicus. You are free to enter.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000450_LYNA<tab>La chambre des Contemplations se trouve derrière la porte du fond. Je l'ai déverrouillée pour vous.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000460_LYNA<tab>Once you have what you require, I'll see it sealed once more. Until then, I will remain without.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000460_LYNA<tab>J'attendrai dehors. Faites-moi savoir quand vous aurez terminé, que je referme la porte à clef.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000470_URIANGER<tab>A moment to collect my thoughts, I prithee...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000470_URIANGER<tab>Si je comprends bien, Exarque...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000480_URIANGER<tab>Thy true name is G'raha Tia, then.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000480_URIANGER<tab>... Pardon, je devrais vous appeler par votre véritable nom... G'raha Tia, c'est ça<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000490_URIANGER<tab>By thy claims, thou too art a native of the Source, though from an age beyond our own, when the Eighth Umbral Calamity hath visited devastation upon our star.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000490_URIANGER<tab>Donc, si je comprends bien, vous êtes originaire non pas du premier reflet, mais du monde primitif... Et d'un futur où le huitième fléau a eu lieu, de surcroît.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000500_URIANGER<tab>Thou hast, by subtle means, reached across the boundaries of time and space to unsow the seeds of catastrophe, ere its creeping vines drag our champion unto an early grave...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000500_URIANGER<tab>Vous avez traversé le temps et l'espace pour prévenir cette catastrophe à la source, et déjouer du même coup le funeste destin promis à <var 08 E905 ((une certaine héroïne)) ((un certain héros)) /var>... Ai-je bien résumé<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000510_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>In essence, yes. A difficult story to swallow, I am sure...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000510_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Oui, tout à fait. Cela fait beaucoup à avaler en une fois, je sais...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000520_URIANGER<tab>(SIGH)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000520_URIANGER<tab>(Respire pro<var 16 /var>fon<var 16 /var>dé<var 16 /var>ment)

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000530_URIANGER<tab>I doubt not the veracity of thy words─not the account of thy coming, nor that of the fated Calamity.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000530_URIANGER<tab>... Non, je vous crois sur parole. Aussi bien en ce qui concerne le huitième fléau que ce que vous m'avez confié à propos de vous.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000540_URIANGER<tab>Yet my mind straineth still to apprehend the enormity of this tale. Wouldst thou favor me with a gradual unfolding of its chapters?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000540_URIANGER<tab>Vos allégations sont d'une gravité sans précédent... Pourriez-vous reprendre votre récit depuis le début, en n'épargnant cette fois aucun détail<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000550_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Certainly.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000550_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Bien sûr.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000551_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>But where to begin? I should start with those great minds who survived the Calamity─Cid Garlond being perhaps the greatest.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000551_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Le début, voyons voir... Je peux te raconter ce qu'il est advenu de Cid Garlond et de ses camarades, après qu'ils ont survécu au chaos sanglant engendré par le fléau.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000560_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>In hopes of staying the unending tides of war, he and his fellows pursued all manner of possible solutions.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000560_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Tandis que la guerre faisait rage et que personne ne semblait en voir le bout, eux se battaient pour trouver un moyen d'y mettre fin.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000570_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>One of these was rooted in a theory which unified several fundamental principles discovered over the course of the Warrior of Light's adventures.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000570_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Avec l'aide <var 08 E905 ((de l'héroïne)) ((du héros)) /var> dont je t'ai parlé, ils finirent par trouver une solution. Ils allaient consacrer le restant de leurs jours à sa mise en œuvre...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000580_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>It proposed a method by which one could enter the river of time, traverse the rift, and leap between worlds.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000580_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Cette solution, tu l'auras deviné, consistait à remonter le cours du temps et à voyager vers un autre monde.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000590_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Perfecting that idea, however, was a work which consumed their lifetimes. And thus was it left to future generations to decide whether theory would be put into practice.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000590_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Lorsqu'enfin la méthode fut au point, ses inventeurs avaient déjà tous atteint le crépuscule de leur vie... Aussi, ils laissèrent à la jeune génération les clefs de leur savoir, ainsi que la décision de s'en servir ou non.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000600_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>But all the while the world continued to burn. Hope was a feeble outpost, beset on all sides by thievery and misery and murder.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000600_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Pendant ce temps, les flammes de la guerre n'en finissaient plus de brûler, consumant les espoirs de chacun dans un tourbillon ininterrompu de violence.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000610_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>People cried out in despair, “There is no hope. We are finished. <var 1A 02 /var>Mankind<var 1A 01 /var> is finished.”
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000610_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>L'humanité tout entière finit par avouer, tête basse, qu'elle avait fait fausse route... que le monde était désormais perdu.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000620_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Then others raised their voices in answer.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000620_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Au milieu de ces turpitudes, une voix s'éleva pourtant.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000630_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>"Though we be beyond salvation, those who came before may yet be saved.“
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000630_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>“Oui, nous sommes condamnés. Mais s'il est une chose pire que la mort, c'est de quitter ce monde sans avoir rien accompli<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000640_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>"We will forge a crossroads, and pave the way for a different future. By the wisdom of our forebears we will prevent this Calamity from ever having come to pass.“
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000640_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Si un autre avenir est possible, alors nous devons nous battre pour qu'il devienne réalité. D'illustres chercheurs nous ont transmis le pouvoir de défaire le huitième fléau, à nous d'en tirer parti.“

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000650_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>The fighting went on unabated, but some few took up Cid's research, and labored to realize those impossible ideas.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000650_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Au milieu du bruit et de la fureur des combats, des hommes et des femmes s'allièrent bientôt, guidés par un même espoir. Ensemble, ils parachevèrent des années durant le travail de Cid et de son équipe.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000660_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>After two centuries of labor, their descendants finally succeeded in awakening the Crystal Tower─an integral part of the process─and in doing so roused its caretaker. Me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000660_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>C'est ainsi qu'environ deux siècles après la catastrophe, ils parvinrent à réactiver la Tour de Cristal, pièce maîtresse de leur projet. Moi qui étais son gardien, c'est à ce moment précis que je rouvris les yeux.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000670_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>By this stage, scholars had largely established the phenomena underpinning the Rejoining, and identified the First as the shard which precipitated the Eighth Umbral Calamity.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000670_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>À l'époque, le mécanisme de déclenchement des fléaux avait déjà été élucidé. Les chercheurs étaient même parvenus à corréler le dernier en date avec l'assimilation du premier reflet.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000680_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>This grand structure was already capable of storing the energies required to attempt the translocation. All that remained was to augment some few of its functions, based upon the theoretical models of Cid and his compeers.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000680_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Entre-temps, la tour avait été en partie remodelée. Elle était dorénavant capable d'emmagasiner assez d'énergie éthérée pour permettre une téléportation entre les mondes.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000690_URIANGER<tab>And by means of such technologies didst thou effect thine arrival in the First, to an age before this star had joined with the Source.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000690_URIANGER<tab>Et c'est vous qui avez été le premier cobaye.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000700_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Some while before, as it turned out. 'Tis all but impossible to predict how time will flow between one world and the next, and we missed our mark by almost an entire century.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000700_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>J'avais dans l'idée de visiter le premier reflet peu avant son assimilation, mais je suis finalement réapparu presque un siècle en avance... Le décalage temporel entre deux mondes est une variable difficile à dompter...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000710_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>But this only worked in our favor. The sin eaters could not be defeated without the blessing of Light, and summoning the only man who might stand a chance against them would require decades of preparation.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000710_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Ceci dit, ce petit sursis s'est avéré salutaire. Les purgateurs ne craignent que ceux qui ont reçu la bénédiction de la Lumière. Dès lors, j'avais besoin de temps pour appeler à moi la bonne personne.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000720_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>But this only worked in our favor. The sin eaters could not be defeated without the blessing of Light, and summoning the only woman who might stand a chance against them would require decades of preparation.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000720_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Ceci dit, ce petit sursis s'est avéré salutaire. Les purgateurs ne craignent que ceux qui ont reçu la bénédiction de la Lumière. Dès lors, j'avais besoin de temps pour appeler à moi la bonne personne.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000730_URIANGER<tab>...An undertaking of scarce credible endurance. That thou hast kept thy plan from falling into disarray these many years bordereth on the miraculous.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000730_URIANGER<tab>Que de chemin parcouru... C'est un vrai miracle que ce plan se soit déroulé sans heurts...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000740_URIANGER<tab>Yet howsoever history be rewritten, thy present self was shaped by events which followed the Calamity.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000740_URIANGER<tab>Vous avez réécrit l'Histoire, mais quelles qu'en soient les répercussions, vous et les habitants de votre monde resterez malgré tout des rescapés du huitième fléau.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000750_URIANGER<tab>Should said catastrophe be averted, the very skein of thine existence will unravel. Surely thou hast foreseen this...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000750_URIANGER<tab>Vous aurez beau l'empêcher, cela ne bouleversera sans doute pas votre destin... Je suppose que vous agissez en con<var 16 /var>nais<var 16 /var>san<var 16 /var>ce de cause.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000760_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I am aware of the consequences. 'Tis for that very reason Cid and his colleagues bequeathed their legacy as an offering...and not an edict.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000760_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Tout à fait. Cid et les siens n'étaient pas dupes non plus, c'est pour cela qu'ils nous ont montré la voie sans nous forcer la main.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000770_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>To give all of oneself for the happiness of others, and with no promise of reward? 'Tis a hard thing to ask.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000770_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Nous avons pris leur suite en sachant pertinemment que nous n'avions rien à y gagner. Ça n'a pas été une décision facile.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000780_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Harder still for those condemned to survive in a world which pitted brother against brother. Indeed, you were right to call the execution of this plan “miraculous”─though the force which held it together was nothing so inexplicable.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000780_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Après tout, qui voudrait défendre corps et âme l'avenir d'autrui alors que son propre monde est en proie à la désolation<var 1D /var>? C'est pourtant ce que nous avons fait, à la mémoire d'une personne...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000790_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>It was him. The Warrior of Light has been our unbroken thread.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000790_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Je vous parle de mon héros, celui dont le récit est devenu un trait d'union entre les peuples.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000800_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>It was her. The Warrior of Light has been our unbroken thread.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000800_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Je vous parle de mon héroïne, celle dont le récit est devenu un trait d'union entre les peuples.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000810_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Where others would stumble and fall, <var 08 E905 ((she)) ((he)) /var> would rise above. Where others would break and run, <var 08 E905 ((she)) ((he)) /var> would carry on.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000810_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Quand la plupart avaient abdiqué face à l'adversité, <var 08 E905 ((elle)) ((lui)) /var> avait continué de se battre. Grâce à sa détermination, une guerre qui ne devait jamais s'achever avait pris fin.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000820_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>The Warrior of Light's tale is one of unyielding bravery. To tell it was to feel courage; to hear it was to feel hope. It was a breath of inspiration in an age of suffocating shadow.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000820_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Sa façon d'avancer contre vents et marées avait presque quelque chose d'insolent... Dans son sillage avaient essaimé des échos porteurs de courage et de réconfort, comme autant de lueurs d'espoir auxquelles se raccrocher en ces temps troublés.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000830_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>In the histories of a fallen nation was our hero hailed as its greatest ally.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000830_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Par la suite, certaines nations sinistrées ont gravé son nom en lettres d'or dans les pages de leur histoire.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000840_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>In the timeworn pages of a noble's memoirs were <var 08 E905 ((her)) ((his)) /var> deeds joyously retold.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000840_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Parfois, ce sont de vieux carnets racornis qui ont conservé la trace de ses exploits.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000850_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>For many, these stories were the flame which warmed them through the coldest of nights.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000850_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Enfin, le récit de ses aventures a accompagné les longues soirées d'hiver de nombreux rescapés.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000860_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>And so it should come as little surprise that the plan found no shortage of volunteers, concerning as it did the Warrior of Light <var 08 E905 ((herself)) ((himself)) /var>. It was their chance to add their own verse to the hero's saga.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000860_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Parmi les partisans du plan de Cid, beaucoup ont exprimé leur volonté d'agir en hommage à leur <var 08 E905 ((défunte héroïne)) ((défunt héros)) /var>.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000870_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>He was the lodestar that brought them all together, to send their final message back through time and space...to him.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000870_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>À leur façon, ils souhaitaient lui laisser un message, comme le témoignage d'un deuil impossible à faire...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000880_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>She was the lodestar that brought them all together, to send their final message back through time and space...to her.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000880_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>À leur façon, ils souhaitaient lui laisser un message, comme le témoignage d'un deuil impossible à faire...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000890_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>"The light of your legacy was our torch in the darkness. Burn bright again...and live.“
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000890_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>“Ô <var 08 E905 ((grande héroïne)) ((grand héros)) /var>, vous nous laissez orphelins. Mais votre legs résonne plus que jamais comme le dernier cri d'espoir de l'humanité.”

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000900_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I am merely the bearer of that wish, come to ensure it is safely delivered.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000900_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>De fait, je ne suis rien de plus qu'un messager chargé de porter leur parole...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000910_URIANGER<tab>Wherefore sharest thou this burden with me and no other? What wouldst thou have me say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000910_URIANGER<tab>Pourquoi n'en avoir parlé à personne d'autre que moi<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000920_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>That you will be my accomplice?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000920_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Très prosaïquement, par intérêt. Navré pour cette approche peu élégante, mais... j'aurais besoin de ton aide.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000930_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>'Twas you yourself who convinced me of your suitability when you spoke of how you learned of the Flood, and of your part in arranging Minfilia's journey to the First.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000930_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Rappelle-toi ce que tu m'as raconté. Que tu avais manœuvré pour permettre la venue de Minfilia dans le premier reflet, avant que ne survienne le déluge de Lumière.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000940_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Your actions showed uncommon resolve. 'Twas clear you were committed to the cause of saving this world.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000940_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Cette décision t'a coûté, j'en suis certain. J'en déduis qu'en ton for intérieur, tu estimes que ce monde vaut véritablement la peine d'être sauvé.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000950_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I knew I could trust you to choose the right path forward...even if that choice came with a heavy price.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000950_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Et même s'il y a pour cela un prix à payer, j'aime à croire que tu iras jusqu'au bout des choses...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000960_URIANGER<tab>...What price?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000960_URIANGER<tab>Un prix à payer...<var 1D /var>? Lequel<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000970_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>When all is said and done, and the last of the Lightwardens lies slain, I will absorb their corrupted aether. And then I will die.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000970_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>En dernier lieu, lorsque le dernier grand purgateur aura rendu l'âme... j'absorberai toute la Lumière excédentaire de ce monde et je disparaîtrai avec.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000980_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Knowing what I know of your companions─not to mention your champion─they will try to stop me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000980_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Si mon plan est éventé, tes camarades risquent de ne pas l'entendre de cette oreille. Je pense notamment à <var 08 E905 ((celle)) ((celui)) /var> que nous attendons toujours. Imagine qu'ils me mettent en échec...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000990_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>But in saving one they would save none.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_000990_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Ce serait dramatique. Nous n'aurions sauvé personne au bout du compte.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001000_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Therefore I implore you to aid me in concealing my identity, and ensuring this tale ends as it must.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001000_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Voilà pourquoi j'aimerais que tu m'aides à protéger mon secret.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001010_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>To this end, I would have you take what I have told you of the Calamity and make of it a portent─a prophetic vision you beheld in the swirling chaos of the rift.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001010_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Tout ce que je viens de te dire à propos du huitième fléau, tu n'as qu'à prétendre l'avoir entendu dans l'interstice qui sépare les mondes. S'il te plaît, Urianger...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001020_URIANGER<tab>...Is this truly thy wish?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001020_URIANGER<tab>Êtes-vous sûr de votre décision<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001030_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>History remembered the Warrior of Light, as I knew it would. And I will suffer no other to rescue the champion whose star has charted my course.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001030_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Le nom de ton ami<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> est devenu synonyme d'espoir dans le futur d'où je viens. C'est un honneur pour moi que de voler à son secours, et je ne céderais ma place pour rien au monde.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001040_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>At this point in time, I yet travel with the Warrior of Light in Eorzea. And I would not have matters here interfere with that of all episodes in my life.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001040_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Sûr et certain. Je ne veux en aucun cas fausser la saveur des aventures que ton ami<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> est en train de vivre dans le monde primitif, en compagnie de mon incarnation passée.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001050_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>At this point in time, the Warrior of Light and I have yet to meet in Eorzea. And I would not wish that meeting soured by events which happen here.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001050_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Sûr et certain. Ton ami<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> doit encore me rencontrer dans le monde primitif, et je tiens à ce que ce moment conserve toute sa fraîcheur et sa spontanéité.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001060_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>I will see this tale to a happy end, my friend. There has been enough tragedy.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001060_MYSTERYVOICE<tab>Quoi qu'il arrive, cette histoire se terminera bien. Tu as ma parole.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001070_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Careful, now.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001070_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Tu le sais sûrement déjà, mais ton état actuel est très préoccupant, pour ne pas dire critique.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001080_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>If you lose control again, the Light could claim you for good.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001080_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Une rechute, et tu risques de te transformer pour de bon en un monstre dénué de conscience.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001090_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Although it's probably only a matter of time before you succumb to the change, in any case.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001090_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>À vrai dire, il est peut-être même déjà trop tard pour te sauver...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001100_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>What do you mean to do?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001100_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Tu comptes faire quoi, sachant tout ça<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q2_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q2_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que répondez-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A2_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>I mean to hunt down Emet-Selch.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A2_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Je ne peux pas laisser Emet-Selch s'en tirer à bon compte.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A2_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>I mean to rescue the Exarch.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A2_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Je veux au moins secourir l'exarque.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A2_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>I mean to have a few words...with both Emet and the Exarch.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A2_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>J'ai deux mots à dire à Emet-Selch... et à l'exarque aussi.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001110_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>(AMUSED HEH)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001110_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>(soupire)

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001120_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Then we should be on our way. The Ascian mentioned the Tempest, did he not?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001120_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Très bien, allons-y alors. Emet-Selch t'a donné rendez-vous dans un lieu appelé La Tempête... Je pense savoir où c'est.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001130_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>That's “the stormy seas around Kholusia” to you. His lair must be down there somewhere, hidden beneath the waves.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001130_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Au large de l'île de Kholusia, là où la mer est balayée par de violentes rafales de vent... Je parie qu'il se planque là-bas.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001140_URIANGER<tab>Ah, we have found thee.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001140_URIANGER<tab>(-Voix familière-)Enfin, nous vous retrouvons.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001150_URIANGER<tab>Word reached us of thy recovery, and thus did we gather with all haste.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001150_URIANGER<tab>On nous a appris que vous étiez sorti<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> du coma, alors nous nous sommes tous réunis pour venir prendre de vos nouvelles.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001160_URIANGER<tab>Ah. By thy looks, I gather thou hast gleaned that which I came to tell thee.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001160_URIANGER<tab>J'allais vous parler de l'exarque, mais j'ai comme l'impression que ce ne sera pas nécessaire... Vous avez vu son passé, n'est-ce pas<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001170_ALPHINAUD<tab>Urianger has shared everything with us─the Exarch's true identity and purpose.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001170_ALPHINAUD<tab>Urianger nous a tout raconté... La véritable identité de l'exarque... Son but inavoué...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001180_URIANGER<tab>I offer no excuses.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001180_URIANGER<tab>Vous avez le droit de m'en vouloir. Je vous ai tu la vérité, et je n'ai rien à dire pour ma défense.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001190_URIANGER<tab>When I agreed to aid the Exarch with his plans, 'twas in full acceptance of the condemnation I would face when my duplicity was laid bare.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001190_URIANGER<tab>Lorsque j'ai accepté d'entrer dans le jeu de l'exarque, j'étais mentalement prêt à subir votre courroux si les masques devaient tomber.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001200_URIANGER<tab>...Yet it is not rancor but resolve that I sense in thee. Thou art fully intent upon walking thy path to its end, art thou not?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001200_URIANGER<tab>Même maintenant, ma résolution n'a pas changé. Seulement, plutôt que de vous laisser me traiter de tous les noms, j'aime autant prendre les devants et faire amende honorable.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001210_URIANGER<tab>If thou canst forgive my deception─or, failing that, set aside thy displeasure for a time─I do beg leave to follow thee. What strength and wisdom I possess are thine to command.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001210_URIANGER<tab>Laissez-moi donc vous accompagner jusqu'au bout de votre périple. Ma force et mon savoir vous seront utiles, j'en suis certain.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q3_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q3_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que répondez-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A3_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>I forgive you. Let's go.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A3_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Très bien, allons-y ensemble.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A3_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>I am a danger to those around me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A3_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Je suis un danger pour vous.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A3_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>No more lies.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A3_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>D'accord, mais ça suffit les cachotteries.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001220_URIANGER<tab>...I thank thee. Doubt not but that I will do all in my power to repay thy kindness, and fulfill the Exarch's wishes.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001220_URIANGER<tab>Merci. Je ferai tout mon possible pour vous revaloir votre grandeur d'âme et exaucer le vœu de l'exarque.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001230_URIANGER<tab>I understand the precarious nature of thy condition. Nonetheless, it is my wish to remain at thy side for as long as I am able.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001230_URIANGER<tab>J'en suis par<var 16 /var>fai<var 16 /var>te<var 16 /var>ment conscient. Malgré cela, je suis prêt à vous suivre aussi longtemps que mes jambes me porteront.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001240_URIANGER<tab>Pray believe me when I say that I took no pleasure in deceiving thee. Indeed, I curse the circumstances which compelled me to do so... But no further secrets lie between us, I swear it.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001240_URIANGER<tab>... Entendu. Si telle est la condition pour que vous tolériez ma présence, je m'y plierai volontiers.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001250_RYNE<tab>I'm sorry but...I don't think this is a good idea.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001250_RYNE<tab>Je... Je ne suis pas d'accord.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001260_RYNE<tab>Leaving the Crystarium, I mean─with or without Urianger.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001260_RYNE<tab>Je ne parle pas du fait qu'Urianger vous accompagne, mais de votre volonté de repartir im<var 16 /var>mé<var 16 /var>dia<var 16 /var>te<var 16 /var>ment à l'aventure... Dans votre état, ce n'est pas raisonnable.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001270_RYNE<tab>What I did for you won't last forever. There's no telling when the Light will break free again.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001270_RYNE<tab>Vous n'êtes pas guéri<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var>. Je n'ai fait que vous prodiguer les premiers soins. Il suffirait d'un rien pour que la Lumière vous consume de nouveau de l'intérieur.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001280_RYNE<tab>Please, you must stay here, at least for a little while longer! We will find a way to cure this, I promise you!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001280_RYNE<tab>Je vous en prie, tenez-vous tranquille pour le moment<var 1D /var>! Je suis sûre qu'on finira par trouver un moyen de vous sauver<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001290_ALISAIE<tab>How can you make promises!? We don't even know where to start!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001290_ALISAIE<tab>Ah oui, et quand ça<var 1D /var>!? Ça fait des semaines qu'on cherche et on n'a toujours pas l'ombre d'une piste<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001300_ALPHINAUD<tab>Alisaie, please. You know Ryne was only trying to help.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001300_ALPHINAUD<tab>Alisaie, Ryne essaie seulement d'aider...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001310_ALISAIE<tab>Of course I know! I know only too well!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001310_ALISAIE<tab>Je sais, je sais... Je comprends par<var 16 /var>fai<var 16 /var>te<var 16 /var>ment son inquiétude... Je ressens exactement la même chose, figure-toi<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001320_ALISAIE<tab>But making promises you have no way of keeping is not a kindness─it's a lie, plain and simple!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001320_ALISAIE<tab>Mais faire des promesses qu'on sait par<var 16 /var>fai<var 16 /var>te<var 16 /var>ment intenables, désolée, je n'appelle pas ça “aider”<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001330_ALISAIE<tab>We've all searched high and low for an answer! And every one of us came back empty-handed!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001330_ALISAIE<tab>On s'est mis en tête de trouver à tout prix une solution avant qu'<var 08 E905 ((elle)) ((il)) /var> ne sorte du coma. On a couru dans tous les sens, toqué à toutes les portes... Tout ça pour rentrer bredouilles.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001340_ALISAIE<tab>I am not about to stand in <var 08 E905 ((her)) ((his)) /var> way now─not after failing <var 08 E905 ((her)) ((him)) /var> in <var 08 E905 ((her)) ((his)) /var> hour of need! No, the least we can do is...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001340_ALISAIE<tab>Je voudrais lui dire de rester sage, moi aussi, mais... je ne peux pas... pas dans ces conditions... Désolée, c'est plus fort que moi<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001350_ALPHINAUD<tab>We will go with you, as well.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001350_ALPHINAUD<tab>Nous venons avec vous.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001360_ALPHINAUD<tab>There is naught to be gained by standing still.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001360_ALPHINAUD<tab>Pour trouver le remède, il faut déjà commencer par le chercher.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001370_YSHTOLA<tab>Indeed, we have exhausted every other avenue.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001370_YSHTOLA<tab>En l'absence de piste sérieuse, ce n'est pas plus mal que tu suives ton instinct.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001380_YSHTOLA<tab>Lead and we shall follow. If there <var 1A 02 /var>is<var 1A 01 /var> any hope to be found, then we will surely find it at your side.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001380_YSHTOLA<tab>Nous, on restera à tes côtés pour te protéger. On guettera la moindre lueur d'espoir.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001390_THANCRED<tab>Are we <var 1A 02 /var>all<var 1A 01 /var> in agreement, then?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001390_THANCRED<tab>Ryne, pas d'objection<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001400_CASSARD<tab>(-???-)Is there aught we can do to help?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001400_CASSARD<tab>Besoin d'un coup de main<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001410_KATLISS<tab>Though we may not know the whole story, we do know you're in for a fight.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001410_KATLISS<tab>Je n'ai pas la moindre idée de ce dont vous débattiez... D'un combat crucial pour notre avenir, je présume<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001420_KATLISS<tab>And while the Exarch's away, it falls to the rest of us to see the Warrior of Darkness is given a proper send-off!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001420_KATLISS<tab>Toujours est-il que c'est à nous de prendre soin <var 08 E905 ((de la Guerrière)) ((du Guerrier)) /var> des Ténèbres en attendant le retour de l'exarque<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001430_ALPHINAUD<tab>You told them!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001430_ALPHINAUD<tab>Lyna, c'est vous qui les avez mis au courant<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001440_LYNA<tab>No! Well...not in so many words.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001440_LYNA<tab>Euh, non, je n'y suis pour rien...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001450_GLYNARD<tab>Aye, we didn't need it spelled out for us. When the night sky appeared over whichever place you went to, it was harder <var 1A 02 /var>not<var 1A 01 /var> to put two and two together!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001450_GLYNARD<tab>Héhé, on a deviné tout seuls, comme des grands<var 1D /var>! Pas besoin d'être détective pour remarquer que la nuit revenait partout où votre ami<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> et vous mettiez les pieds<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001460_BRAGI<tab>From the moment I heard that you and the Exarch shared a homeland, I had my suspicions.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001460_BRAGI<tab>Moi, je m'en suis douté dès le moment où on nous l'a décrit<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> comme un<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> compatriote de l'exarque.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001470_BRAGI<tab>Long had he been waiting for a certain someone to arrive...and I knew at once that it must be you.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001470_BRAGI<tab>Aussi loin que je me souvienne, il était toujours là à attendre fébrilement la venue de quelqu'un... Je me suis dit que ça devait être ce quelqu'un.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001480_CRYSTARIUMGATEKEEPER<tab>Exactly! When he went out to meet you, 'twas clear it was no ordinary visitor.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001480_CRYSTARIUMGATEKEEPER<tab>M-moi aussi, je m'en doutais<var 1D /var>! Quand l'exarque est allé pour la première fois à votre rencontre, j'ai tout de suite compris que vous n'étiez pas n'importe qui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001490_CRYSTARIUMGATEKEEPER<tab>That spring in his step spoke volumes. I could feel his excitement!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001490_CRYSTARIUMGATEKEEPER<tab>Il était tellement fou de joie qu'il courait en faisant des sauts de cabri... J'avais jamais vu ça de ma vie<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001500_CRYSTARIUMWOMAN<tab>Me too!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001500_CRYSTARIUMWOMAN<tab>Pareil pour moi<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001510_CRYSTARIUMMAN<tab>That's right!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001510_CRYSTARIUMMAN<tab>Et moi<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001520_CRYSTARIUMOLDMAN<tab>Hear, hear!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001520_CRYSTARIUMOLDMAN<tab>Je confirme<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001530_MOREN<tab>We do not fully understand where you or the Exarch hail from, or why you've all done so much to protect us.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001530_MOREN<tab>Nous ignorons tout de vous et de l'exarque... Nous ne savons ni d'où vous venez, ni ce qui vous pousse à faire preuve de tant de générosité envers nous.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001540_MOREN<tab>But we are deeply grateful, nonetheless.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001540_MOREN<tab>Mais une chose est sûre<var 1D /var>: nous vous sommes re<var 16 /var>con<var 16 /var>nais<var 16 /var>sants, et vous remercions du fond du cœur.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001550_MOREN<tab>So if there is anything at all we might do to aid your journey, you need only name it. What would you have of us?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001550_MOREN<tab>C'est pourquoi nous ne voulons pas rester spectateurs. Si l'exarque est en difficulté, nous vous aiderons à le tirer de là. Donnez-nous un rôle à jouer, s'il vous plaît. N'importe lequel<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001560_YSHTOLA<tab>You might have invited them to join us, were there not so many. But come, they are waiting. What is your will, O Warrior of Darkness?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001560_YSHTOLA<tab>Ça va être difficile d'emmener tout ce monde avec nous... Enfin, à toi de voir, <var 08 E905 ((Guerrière)) ((Guerrier)) /var> des Ténèbres<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q4_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q4_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que répondez-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A4_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Defend the Crystarium until we return!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A4_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Protégez cette cité en attendant notre retour<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A4_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Leave it to us─we'll see the Exarch home safe and sound!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A4_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Je ramènerai l'exarque, vous avez ma parole<var 1D /var>! En attendant, je vous confie Cristarium<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A4_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>Hope for the best, but prepare for the worst...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A4_000_003_NONE_VOICE<tab>Restez ici en renfort... et soyez prêts à affronter le pire.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001570_URIANGER<tab>[O great and serene Bismarck.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001570_URIANGER<tab><var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Ô grand Bismarck, toi qui par ta présence illumines ces lieux...<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001580_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)[Long has it been since my name was called.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001580_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)<var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Oh... Il y a longtemps qu'un humain ne m'avait point adressé la parole...<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001590_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)[Why do you wake me, little neighbor?]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001590_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)<var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Que veux-tu, frêle voyageur<var 1D /var>?<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001600_URIANGER<tab>[To the bottom of the western sea we go. Pray lend us your back and your breath.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001600_URIANGER<tab><var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Atteindre le fond des mers de l'ouest. Nous voudrions grimper sur ton dos et profiter de ton souffle magique.<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001610_BISMARCK<tab>(GRUMBLE)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001610_BISMARCK<tab><var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Hmm...<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001620_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)[This world is in twilight. I wait for the sun to set. I wish only to sleep.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001620_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)<var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Ce monde est à son crépuscule. Il sombrera bien assez tôt. Laissez-moi dormir.<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001630_ALISAIE<tab>Oh dear. I don't need to speak Fae to know that didn't go well...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001630_ALISAIE<tab>Je ne comprends pas un mot de ce qu'ils racontent, mais Bismarck n'a pas l'air très coopératif...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q5_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q5_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que dites-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A5_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>I know what to do!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A5_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>J'ai une idée<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A5_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>We need Feo Ul!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A5_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Feo Ul, aide-nous<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001640_FEOUL<tab>(LAUGH)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001640_FEOUL<tab>Me voilà<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001641_FEOUL<tab>My [adorable sapling]! You've learned to call me at last!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001641_FEOUL<tab>C'est bien, je vois que mon <var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>petit arbrisseau<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var> apprend de ses erreurs<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001650_FEOUL<tab>And where do you go? On a trip? A journey? I <var 1A 02 /var>knew<var 1A 01 /var> you wouldn't give up without a fight!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001650_FEOUL<tab>Et qu'il a décidé d'aller de l'avant... Héhé, je n'en attendais pas moins de lui<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001660_FEOUL<tab>Oh, my precious mortal. I shall help you in any way I can!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001660_FEOUL<tab>Pauvre <var 08 E905 ((petite)) ((petit)) /var>, comme je te plains... Ne crains rien, ta jolie branchette va prendre les choses en main<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001670_FEOUL<tab>[Sleepy Bismarck, you old pixie! These are my precious, precious saplings.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001670_FEOUL<tab><var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Oh<var 1D /var>! Bismarck, vieux ronfleur<var 1D /var>! Ces gens sont tous mes précieux petits arbrisseaux<var 1D /var>!<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001680_FEOUL<tab>[Let their wish be the king's command.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001680_FEOUL<tab><var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Leur volonté est aussi celle de ton monarque, compris<var 1D /var>?<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001690_BISMARCK<tab>(GRUMBLE)
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001690_BISMARCK<tab>(longue expiration)

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001700_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)[What a rare thing to awaken to.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001700_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)<var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Je me réveille, et qui vois-je<var 1D /var>?<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001710_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)[My beautiful king. If it be thy wish, then so shall it be done.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001710_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)<var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Votre resplendissante Altesse... Vos désirs sont des ordres.<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001720_FEOUL<tab>Be sure to scrub this one's teeth for him upon your return. It's only good manners.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001720_FEOUL<tab>À votre retour, n'oubliez pas de le remercier comme il se doit, en lui brossant les dents avec des cendres.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001730_URIANGER<tab>It will be done, Your Majesty. Our deepest thanks for your timely intervention.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001730_URIANGER<tab>Nous n'y manquerons pas. Merci infiniment pour votre in<var 16 /var>ter<var 16 /var>ven<var 16 /var>tion, Votre Altesse.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001740_FEOUL<tab>An agreement is reached, and your departure is at hand! You wingless ones best hold on tight!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001740_FEOUL<tab>Vous avez votre moyen de transport, alors en route<var 1D /var>! Agrippez-vous bien pour ne pas tomber à l'eau<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001750_FEOUL<tab>May the blessings of the fae keep you safe, [shining souls]!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001750_FEOUL<tab>Que la bénédiction du royaume féérique accompagne votre périple. Revenez sains et saufs, mes chères <var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>âmes scintillantes<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var><var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001760_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)[To the western sea we go. Wrapped in my breath, I will see you to your destination, little neighbors.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001760_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)<var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Cap sur les mers de l'ouest. Une fois arrivés à destination, frêles voyageurs, je vous envelopperai de mon souffle.<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001770_IRVITHE<tab>And just like that, it's all gone back to the way it was...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001770_IRVITHE<tab>En fin de compte, tout est redevenu comme avant...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001780_GRITHIL<tab>What was you expecting? Hundred years of honey and rainbows?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001780_GRITHIL<tab>Un pas en avant, deux pas en arrière... C'est la vie, on n'y peut rien...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001790_GRITHIL<tab>Seeing them Eulmore types wake up and smell the ashes was miracle enough for me.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001790_GRITHIL<tab>Que les Eulmoriens aient ravalé leur fierté, c'est déjà une belle revanche sur l'Histoire, je trouve.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001800_IRVITHE<tab>Ah, but the magic in the air when that Ladder started moving...hah! And when that great hulking Talos rose up, <var 1A 02 /var>gods<var 1A 01 /var>...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001800_IRVITHE<tab>Et qu'est-ce que tu fais du frisson qu'on a tous ressenti quand L'Échelle s'est mise en branle<var 1D /var>? Quand le talos géant s'est levé<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001810_IRVITHE<tab>I could live a thousand years and never behold anything so amazing...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001810_IRVITHE<tab>J'peux pas croire que ça comptait pour du beurre...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001820_GRITHIL<tab>What the─! Do you see that!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001820_GRITHIL<tab>Ouaaah<var 1D /var>! C'est quoi c'bestiau<var 1D /var>!?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001830_IRVITHE<tab>What a monster! Where did it even come from!?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001830_IRVITHE<tab>Mazette<var 1D /var>! Ça, c'est ce que j'appelle un gros poisson<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001840_GRITHIL<tab>Uh, wha... Wh-Whoa there...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001840_GRITHIL<tab>Euh, attends... Tu vois ce que je vois<var 1D /var>!?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001850_IRVITHE<tab>It's not stopping...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001850_IRVITHE<tab>Oh non, c'est pas vrai...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001860_IRVITHE<tab>Run! <var 1A 02 /var>Run<var 1A 01 /var>!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001860_IRVITHE<tab>Tous aux abris<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001870_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)[I have fulfilled my duty. I return now to the lake.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001870_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)<var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>J'ai tenu parole. Je vais à présent regagner mes eaux.<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001880_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)[I have not flown in an age. It was...pleasant. May your journey be a safe one, little neighbors.]
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001880_BISMARCK<tab>(-Bismarck-)<var 48 F20243 /var><var 49 F20244 /var>Me dégourdir les ailes m'a fait du bien. Que la fortune vous sourie, frêles voyageurs...<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var>

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001890_RYNE<tab>Wow...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001890_RYNE<tab>Incroyable...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001900_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>The breath of Bismarck. See how it swells to form a dome beneath the waves...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001900_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Le souffle de Bismarck avait créé une gigantesque bulle d'air, là, tout au fond de l'abysse liquide.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001910_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>The waters recede. The Tempest's floor is laid bare.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001910_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>La Tempête, théâtre de notre ultime combat, était mise à nu.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001920_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>In defiance of the blinding sky, this place holds fast to its gloom.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001920_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Du ciel de nouveau empli de Lumière, ce lieu était le négatif, sombre et inhospitalier.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001930_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>The last refuge of he who denies the Light with every fiber of his being.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001930_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>On pouvait y voir sans peine le refuge d'un homme que le trop-plein de clarté avait effarouché.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001940_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>You stand at the precipice, hero. Journey unto the Heart of Darkness. Finish it.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001940_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Une âme vaillante s'apprêtait à en franchir le palier, prête à y vivre sa dernière aventure...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001950_READEROFONDO<tab>O stewards of the Ondo... We offer up our light in answer...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001950_READEROFONDO<tab>Ô dieu protecteur, contemple cccette flamme et entends nos prières...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001960_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>That crystal you showed the artisan...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001960_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Dis, à propos du cristal que tu as montré à cet artisan...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001970_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Was it...? Did it belong to one of my friends?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001970_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Appartenait-il par hasard... à l'un de mes camarades<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q6_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>What will you say?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_Q6_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Que répondez-vous<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A6_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>I thought you were always watching?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A6_000_001_NONE_VOICE<tab>Tu ne surveilles pas tout ce que je fais<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A6_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Miss that part, did you?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_A6_000_002_NONE_VOICE<tab>Tu as loupé un épisode, on dirait...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001980_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I try to give you a <var 1A 02 /var>measure<var 1A 01 /var> of privacy... No one wants a spirit looking over their shoulder every moment of the day.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001980_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Excuse-moi de respecter ton intimité<var 1D /var>! Qu'est-ce que tu croyais, que j'allais te coller aux basques à longueur de journée<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001990_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>So tell me, if you would. How did you come across that crystal?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_001990_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Allez, dis-moi... D'où vient ce cristal<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002000_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>It was Renda-Rae's, then...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002000_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Alors comme ça, c'est celui de Renda-Rae<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002010_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>It was Nyelbert's, then...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002010_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Alors comme ça, c'est celui de Nyelbert<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002020_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>It was Branden's, then...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002020_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Alors comme ça, c'est celui de Branden<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002030_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>It was Lamitt's, then...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002030_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Alors comme ça, c'est celui de Lamitt<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002040_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I was right, then...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002040_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>C'était donc bien un de leurs cristaux...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002050_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I was right, then...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002050_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Alors comme ça, c'est son cristal...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002060_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Strange that I should learn such things now, after they're long gone. They were fine friends, every one of them...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002060_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Et c'est maintenant que je découvre ce que mes camarades avaient sur le cœur... Du début à la fin, ils ne m'auront jamais déçu.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002070_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I didn't expect death to teach me so much.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002070_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Décidément, c'est fou tout ce qu'on peut apprendre après sa mort...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002080_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>About them, about Seto─about you. About the hope that hides at the heart of this world.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002080_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Sur toi, sur Seto... Et aussi sur mon monde. Je réalise à présent à quel point il était tenace et rempli d'espoir.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002090_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I've never been one for idle chitchat, but if by some miracle I could see them all again, I doubt I'd ever stop talking...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002090_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>Je ne suis pas doué pour raconter des histoires... mais si ma route recroise un jour celle de mes frères et sœurs d'armes, je tâcherai au moins de leur faire savoir ça.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002100_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>I'm grateful I got to bend your ear, at least. And just for that, I reckon I'll stick with you...to the very end.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002100_WARRIOROFDARKNESS<tab>... Merci pour tout, vraiment. Je n'ai plus qu'une envie, c'est de t'escorter jusqu'au bout de ton périple.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002110_ALPHINAUD<tab>Apologies─we were a little late to the gathering.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002110_ALPHINAUD<tab>Désolé, on est en retard.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002120_YSHTOLA<tab>It seems we've succeeded in gaining their trust.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002120_YSHTOLA<tab>On a réussi à gagner leur confiance, on dirait.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002130_THANCRED<tab>The delay wasn't exactly welcome, but at least our many hands made light work.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002130_THANCRED<tab>J'avais mes réserves quant à notre plan... Mais on a bien fait de se retrousser les manches, finalement.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002140_THANCRED<tab>And they seemed especially impressed with your contribution. Our hero, indeed.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002140_THANCRED<tab>Comme quoi, ça paye de faire preuve de bonne foi.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002150_ALPHINAUD<tab>Y'shtola was telling us those structures may date back to the age of the Ascians.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002150_ALPHINAUD<tab>... Y'shtola nous a appris que ce bâtiment datait peut-être du temps des Asciens.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002160_ALISAIE<tab>An Ascian homeland...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002160_ALISAIE<tab>La cité des Asciens...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002170_ALISAIE<tab>Despite his many protestations, I never quite believed Emet-Selch was telling the truth.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002170_ALISAIE<tab>La peinture qu'Emet-Selch en a faite m'avait laissée songeuse, mais là...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002180_ALPHINAUD<tab>Nor I. But there is no denying the evidence before our eyes. Clearly, this was once a great city...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002180_ALPHINAUD<tab>Oui... En admirant ce vestige, on réalise à quel point leur architecture devait être grandiose.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002190_ALPHINAUD<tab>...A home they would see restored, no matter how many tens of thousands of years it takes.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002190_ALPHINAUD<tab>Le temps n'a pas eu raison de leur attachement à cette époque. Au contraire, ils désirent plus que jamais ressusciter leur précieux paradis perdu...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002200_ALISAIE<tab>It's a hollow dream, when you think about it. Even if they manage to rejoin all the worlds, they'll never bring back the ones who were lost.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002200_ALISAIE<tab>C'est absurde... Ils vont réunifier les mondes, et après<var 1D /var>? Ce n'est pas ça qui ramènera leurs proches à la vie...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002210_ALISAIE<tab>But would I have done any different...?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002210_ALISAIE<tab>À leur place... je me demande ce que je ferais...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002220_RYNE<tab>Are you...? How are you feeling?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002220_RYNE<tab>Et vous, ça va en ce moment<var 1D /var>? Vous n'êtes pas trop fatigué<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var><var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002230_YSHTOLA<tab>You have completed your devotions?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002230_YSHTOLA<tab>Ça y est, vous avez fini de prier<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002240_READEROFONDO<tab>Yesss... To the honored ancientsss have we offered up our prayers and our gratitude. You, too, have our thanks.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002240_READEROFONDO<tab>Fssshh... Oui. Les anccciens ont reçççu nos ressspectueuses pensssées. Merccci encore pour votre particccipation.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002250_URIANGER<tab>Might we trouble thee then to tell us more of the illuminated land of which thou didst lately speak?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002250_URIANGER<tab>Voulez-vous bien nous en dire plus sur cette fameuse “étendue nitescente”, à présent<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002260_READEROFONDO<tab>To the west of here lies a great trench. Some days ago, a light appeared in that endlesss darknesss.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002260_READEROFONDO<tab>Fssshh... Il y a quelques jours, une vive lueur est apparue au fond de la grande fosse sssous-marine, à l'ouessst d'iccci.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002270_READEROFONDO<tab>Curiousss, we ventured closer...and discovered in the depths an entire city.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002270_READEROFONDO<tab>Nous avons accouru pour voir cccela de plus près. Ccc'est alors que nous avons découvert... une gigantesssque cccité.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002280_READEROFONDO<tab>The buildings we spied were akin to our own everlasting abodes. Impossibly so.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002280_READEROFONDO<tab>D'assspect, elle ressemblait en tout point à nos immarcccessibles demeures.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002290_READEROFONDO<tab>We understood at once─the ancients had risen. There could be no doubt.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002290_READEROFONDO<tab>Pour nous, cccela ne faisait aucun doute<var 1D /var>: les anccciens étaient de retour.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002300_READEROFONDO<tab>Taken with terror, we retreated to the Cupsss, and I decreed that none should enter the trench until such time as we received a sssign.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002300_READEROFONDO<tab>De peur, nous sssommes rentrés en hâte à Baïne, et avons décccidé de ne plus nous aventurer là-bas à moins qu'un sssigne du dessstin ne nous y invite.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002310_ALPHINAUD<tab>Might it still be possible to reach this city of the ancients?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002310_ALPHINAUD<tab>Est-il encore possible de s'y rendre à l'heure actuelle<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002320_READEROFONDO<tab>Hm... With no water to drown you, a finless one could now travel there, yesss.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002320_READEROFONDO<tab>Fssshh... Oui, maintenant qu'il n'y a plus d'eau, même des sssans nageoires comme vous peuvent y faire un tour.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002330_READEROFONDO<tab>I am convinced you are the sssign for which we have been waiting. My people will show you the way.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002330_READEROFONDO<tab>J'aime à croire que votre venue est providentielle, je vais donc vous aider, en commençççant par vous trouver un guide.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002340_ALPHINAUD<tab>Shall we?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002340_ALPHINAUD<tab>On est partis<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002350_ALISAIE<tab>By the gods!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002350_ALISAIE<tab>Pincez-moi, je rêve<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002360_ALPHINAUD<tab>When the Ondo spoke of a city, I did not think they meant an actual city!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002360_ALPHINAUD<tab>Je comprends mieux pourquoi les Ondos ont pris peur... Cette cité est gigantesque<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002370_YSHTOLA<tab>Then...we are seeing the same view.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002370_YSHTOLA<tab>Vous pouvez donc la voir, vous aussi...

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002380_YSHTOLA<tab>The remnants in the Ondo settlement were solid, material structures, but these...
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002380_YSHTOLA<tab>C'est vrai qu'elle ressemble aux vestiges qu'on a vus au village ondo... À une différence près<var 1D /var>: les vestiges étaient réels, eux.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002390_YSHTOLA<tab>Everything here pulses with aether. 'Tis an enchantment on a monumental scale!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002390_YSHTOLA<tab>Là, on a affaire à une illusion à grande échelle... Une cité-mirage, si vous préférez, érigée à même la fosse océanique<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002400_EMETSELCH<tab>This really is unacceptable. I gave you very specific instructions.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002400_EMETSELCH<tab>Pas si vite, chers visiteurs. Vous êtes ici dans un haut lieu de la cité. Il y a des règles strictes à observer.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002410_ALPHINAUD<tab>Emet-Selch!
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002410_ALPHINAUD<tab>Emet-Selch<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002420_EMETSELCH<tab>My invitation was for an abomination, ripe with the power to bring about the world's annihilation.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002420_EMETSELCH<tab>Dis donc, tu te moques de moi<var 1D /var>? Il m'a semblé avoir invité un monstre, <var 08 E905 ((la fossoyeuse)) ((le fossoyeur)) /var> de ce monde, pas... ça.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002430_EMETSELCH<tab>Not this half-broken...thing. Whatever am I to do with you?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002430_EMETSELCH<tab>Tu es loin, très loin du compte, là... Tant que tu réfrènes ton pouvoir, tu ne m'es d'aucune utilité. Tu le sais, ça.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002440_EMETSELCH<tab>And I see you insist on keeping the same familiar company. Are you so lost without them?
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002440_EMETSELCH<tab>D'ailleurs, que fais-tu encore avec ces gêneurs<var 1D /var>? Ce sont tes futurs ennemis, je te rappelle. La solitude t'effraie donc à ce point<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002450_YSHTOLA<tab>It is not <var 1A 02 /var><var 08 E905 ((she)) ((he)) /var><var 1A 01 /var> who is lost without the familiar.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002450_YSHTOLA<tab>On te retourne la question, Emet-Selch.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002460_YSHTOLA<tab>Not content with remaking an entire city, you aim to fill it with the reconstituted souls of the dead.
target: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002460_YSHTOLA<tab>Pour faire apparaître cette cité, et vouloir en plus y ressusciter ceux qui ont été sacrifiés à Zordiarche, tu dois vraiment être en mal de compagnie.

source: TEXT_VOICEMAN_05005_002470_EMETSELCH<tab>I may have gotten a <var 1A 02 /var>little<var 1A 01 /var> carried away, in my attention to detail. Added a few unnecessary flourishes...
